title: Emergency Preparedness for Flooding Events in Ottawa, ON
subtitle: with ArcGIS Web AppBuilder

about.aboutContent:
This app is created as a requirement for the ECCE challenge 2022. It is developed by Stanley Ho and Jayden Chang of Western University, Canada.
This map aims for three objectives:
  1. Visualize affected area in case of a flooding event, where we are picking Ottawa as our study area.
  2. Provide locations for public services (e.g., sandbags distribution site, civil defense facilities)
  3. In case there is a need to evacuate resident from vulnerable area, provide navigation to the nearest safe, potential shelter (e.g., schools, community centres)

All data used are open sources from the Government of Canada, Government of Ontario, or the City of Ottawa.
